<subSubSection id="E57198FEBC9F66D88EB9E570671C893A" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="8F41F7BF4289347971FF7AA14FB54551" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A8D30F6578F5FB250AD7C9FCAE4E3DBC" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
The subfamily and tribal position of 
<taxonomicName id="E3CD42548710A7C53EC303B15AB4BF62" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Holcophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holcophora" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Holcophora</taxonomicName>
is still somewhat uncertain. Meyrick placed 
<taxonomicName id="14C1FCDBCAE7AA01EEB54435C1E1A1F5" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Holcophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holcophora" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Holcophora</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0F88876FBE43EB2CC7D5A6D91DE66DBE" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Aponoea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aponoea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aponoea</taxonomicName>
, separated only by 
<taxonomicName id="4B7358BC6A22AF124059F40E8CEDAF15" authority="Staudinger, 1871" authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Rhynchopacha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rhynchopacha" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Rhynchopacha</taxonomicName>
Staudinger, 1871 (= 
<taxonomicName id="4ED599A5ACFB399C4D05F8EF4C8FE98A" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Athrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Athrips" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Athrips</taxonomicName>
Billberg, 1820), in his 'Group 7 (
<taxonomicName id="C91BDDF39C80280FE489EB2CD8D91067" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Dichomeris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dichomeris" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dichomeris</taxonomicName>
type)' (= 
<taxonomicName id="C1E879F94C56376337D509F6103E0C3D" lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Dichomeridinae">Dichomeridinae</taxonomicName>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="5D2EF54479CCF7811F7AFBE7DC94CD6F" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Karsholt et al. (1996</bibRefCitation>
: 120) in 
<taxonomicName id="68E72BD3E56DA62C831E1CB448B03F7B" lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Gelechiinae">Gelechiinae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="2A0613C360D80678F1725D96E88A91B9" lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="tribe" tribe="Chelariini">Chelariini</taxonomicName>
). We follow 
<bibRefCitation id="2C3D4B90845204F73035C3CDCE4583F4" author="Ponomarenko, MG" journalOrPublisher="Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" pagination="135 - 142" title="Functional morphology of the male genitalia in the gelechiid-moth genera Holcophora Stgr., Ananarsia Ams., and Nothris Hbn. (Lepidoptera, Gelechiidae: Gelechiini, Dichomeridini)." volume="88" year="2009">Ponomarenko (2009</bibRefCitation>
: 195, English translation), who placed 
<taxonomicName id="700D82646C70F9545CB8B60BF4EB7B97" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Holcophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holcophora" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Holcophora</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="9A65CBC5C970F230AEFAB9DD4D4DB344" lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Gelechiinae">Gelechiinae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="511F35A0602A18FF13ED6608EEC9EE56" lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="tribe" tribe="Gelechiini">Gelechiini</taxonomicName>
), based on specifics of the male genitalia musculature.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
